India’s Short-Term Challenge Is to Curb Inflation, Singh Says

-- B y   B i b h u d a t t a   P r a d h a n
-- 
2011-10-11T09:09:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/india-s-short-term-challenge-is-to-curb-inflation-singh-says.html
The Indian government’s challenge in
the short term is to bring down inflation, Prime Minister
 Manmohan Singh  said in a conference in  New Delhi  today.  “The fundamentals of our economy remain strong. Despite
the global slowdown, we will still achieve a growth rate of
close to 8 percent this year,” Singh said in an e-mailed copy
of his speech at the Combined Commanders’ Conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bibhudatta Pradhan in New Delhi at 
 bpradhan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
